BBUUGGSS
     On BSD systems, the _-_s option reports sizes that are half the  cor-
     rect  values for files that are NFS-mounted from HP-UX systems.  On
     HP-UX systems, it reports sizes that are twice the  correct  values
     for  files that are NFS-mounted from BSD systems.  This is due to a
     flaw in HP-UX; it also affects the HP-UX llss program.

     The long-named options can be introduced with `+' as well as  `--',
     for  compatibility  with previous releases.  Eventually support for
     `+' will be removed, because it is incompatible  with  the  POSIX.2
     standard.
